The user is editing a class named 'CountStepsNotCompletedService' which includes methods for handling various stages of an application process. The user is also running tests for this class, as indicated by the 'Running tests' section at the bottom of the IDE. This suggests the user is involved in backend development and testing.

The third screenshot shows the user continuing to work in IntelliJ IDEA, focusing on the 'CountStepsNotCompletedServiceTests' class. The user is writing and running integration tests to ensure that all steps in the application process are completed correctly. The visible code includes assertions to verify the correct behavior of the application at different stages. This further confirms the user's role in backend development and testing.
